body:
Related to #3005 
I'm using the latest trunk version.


Testcase( same as #3005 ):
```verilog
module t #( parameter NV = 2500) (
    input          a,
    input          w1,
    input  [127:0] w2,
    output [ 31:0] o
);

wire [NV-1:0] d = a ? NV'(0) : {NV{w2}};
assign        o = d[31:0];

endmodule
```
(1) using default --expand-limit 64
```cpp
VL_INLINE_OPT void Vdemo___024root___combo__TOP__1(Vdemo___024root* vlSelf) {
    if (false && vlSelf) {}  // Prevent unused
    Vdemo__Syms* const __restrict vlSymsp VL_ATTR_UNUSED = vlSelf->vlSymsp;
    VL_DEBUG_IF(VL_DBG_MSGF("+    Vdemo___024root___combo__TOP__1\n"); );
    // Init
    VlWide<10000>/*319999:0*/ __Vtemp_h6b1a2e61__0;
    VlWide<10000>/*319999:0*/ __Vtemp_h16568e56__0;
    // Body
    VL_REPLICATE_WWI(320000,128,32, __Vtemp_h6b1a2e61__0, vlSelf->w2, 0x9c4U);
    VL_COND_WIWW(320000,1,320000,320000, __Vtemp_h16568e56__0, (IData)(vlSelf->a), Vdemo__ConstPool__CONST_hcca85584_0, __Vtemp_h6b1a2e61__0);
    vlSelf->o = __Vtemp_h16568e56__0[0U];
}

```
(2) using --expand-limit 100000
```cpp
VL_INLINE_OPT void Vdemo___024root___combo__TOP__1(Vdemo___024root* vlSelf) {
    if (false && vlSelf) {}  // Prevent unused
    Vdemo__Syms* const __restrict vlSymsp VL_ATTR_UNUSED = vlSelf->vlSymsp;
    VL_DEBUG_IF(VL_DBG_MSGF("+    Vdemo___024root___combo__TOP__1\n"); );
    // Body
    vlSelf->o = ((IData)(vlSelf->a) ? Vdemo__ConstPool__CONST_hcca85584_0[0U]
                  : vlSelf->w2[0U]);
}
```

As you can see, using --expand-limit 100000 would generate cleaner and faster code.
The `VL_REPLICATE_WWI` and `VL_COND_WIWW` code generated by the default --expand-limit setting contains large for-loops , which is much slower.

I guess the default setting --expand-limit should also have the ability to optimize and generate the same clean code. So this may be a point that verilator can do better.
